annotationA: Dynactin 5, p25 subunit; It is involved in the biological process described with: spermatogenesis; positive regulation of retrograde axon cargo transport; microtubule-based movement
annotationB: Dynactin subunit 2; Modulates cytoplasmic dynein binding to an organelle, and plays a role in prometaphase chromosome alignment and spindle organization during mitosis. May play a role in synapse formation during brain development (By similarity)
